info.author: Sylvain Fourmanoit
info.description:
pyevas is a C extension module allowing the use of the Evas
library[1] from a Python environment. It aims at providing full
support for the original functionalities from the C procedural API,
wrapped to have a pythonic look and feel. See the module 
documentation for details.
